;; Tier-2 REASONING-COST task suite — the machine-readable source of truth for the
;; harness. Prose: METHODOLOGY.md. Sibling SAFETY-axis experiment: ../concurrent-authoring/
;; (do NOT conflate; this is the COST axis — a single agent, no concurrency).
;; Validity audit this design satisfies: ../owned-resolution-audit/REPORT.md (Q4).
;;
;; THE METRIC: retrieval OPERATIONS to reach the SAME verified-correct answer, NOT
;; wall-clock. One primitive retrieval = one op = one oplog line.
;;   TEXT arm  primitives:  tsearch <regex> [path]   (one source search  -> 1 op; ALTERNATION
;;                                                     inside one regex is ONE pass = 1 op)
;;                          tread   <file> [a:b]      (one file/range read -> 1 op)
;;   GRAPH arm primitive:   gquery  <op> {...}        (one daemon socket round-trip -> 1 op)
;; The wrappers CANNOT batch (no raw shell in the text arm); wc -l <arm>.oplog == op count.
;;
;; TWO LAYERS (they prove DIFFERENT things):
;;   A = deterministic structural-cost. A PROOF about THIS corpus (the minimal-correct text
;;       reconstruction, justified op-by-op, no agent in the loop). Model-INDEPENDENT because
;;       the agent is REMOVED -> it proves the FLOOR, not what an agent does. Authored numbers.
;;   B = real paired sub-agents. The ONLY empirical claim. N>=10 per task per arm; report the
;;       DISTRIBUTION (min/median/max op-count + correct-rate). Substrate-blind stopping rule.
;;       Wrapper-confined (NO Bash/Read/Grep) + bypass-detector (discard transcript if
;;       observed-retrievals != wc -l oplog). The HEADLINE empirical sentence is a B distribution.
;;
;; AMORTIZATION FRAME (applied to BOTH arms symmetrically): WARM session is the precondition
;; of the per-query claim. The graph's setup (~37s, measured) is paid ONCE; SYMMETRICALLY the
;; text arm learns each module's alias ONCE (the :learned-alias map is given to both arms at
;; setup) and reuses it -> alias-discovery is NOT a per-task op. In a COLD single-question
;; session the graph LOSES (pays ~37s for one query); we say so.
;;
;; OWNED-RESOLUTION VALIDITY (the experiment-invalidating trap — all four ENFORCED & VERIFIED):
;;   (i)   daemon populated with the corpus AS CLAIMS once, at setup (the .bclj->EDN->flat-log
;;         projection seeds the temp log the daemon boots from). NOT per query.
;;         VERIFIED: 101671 live corpus claims in the warm store (not a 4-claim proxy).
;;   (ii)  every graph-arm retrieval = one gquery socket round-trip and NOTHING else; the
;;         wrapper is structurally incapable of shelling racket --emit-edn / resolve.clj.
;;         -> NO :resolver-callgraph under :substrates :graph (it is the ORACLE, computed once).
;;   (iii) LIVE graph headline = (a)+(b) only (served off warm refers_to via daemon :callers —
;;         VERIFIED nonempty for both). (c)/(d) are DETERMINISTIC-LAYER-ONLY with the graph cost
;;         a labeled HYPOTHETICAL (the unbuilt :reaches/:type-refs op), VISUALLY SEGREGATED from
;;         the live a/b rows. VERIFIED: {:op :reaches}/{:op :type-refs} -> {:error "unknown op"}.
;;         Routing (c)/(d) through the cold callgraph CLI AS A GRAPH-ARM RETRIEVAL is FORBIDDEN.
;;   (iv)  boot guard in reproduce.sh: :status claim-count nonzero AND :log == our temp log
;;         AND :callers of a known target nonempty, BEFORE any measurement. FAIL LOUD otherwise.
;;         VERIFIED live (see :graph-setup :boot-guard-observed).
;;
;; EVERY coordinate below is MEASURED against the live corpus (src/fram, 11 modules). The raw
;; numbers were re-verified during this revision (commands in :measured-by per task):
;;   - kernel.bclj:101  (defrecord Claim [l :- String p :- String r :- String]) -> warm node @kernel#298
;;   - `Claim` has THREE live spellings (one identity): Claim x39, k/Claim x29, k/->Claim x6 (=74 tokens);
;;     a SINGLE alternation regex `(k/)?(->)?Claim\b` catches all three in ONE pass (VERIFIED).
;;   - 6 modules alias fram.kernel :as k (export fold import main query tools); datalog/schema do NOT.
;;   - 41 `(Vec Claim)`/`(Vec k/Claim)` annotation SITES in SOURCE (=20 (Vec Claim) + 21 (Vec k/Claim),
;;     VERIFIED); erase to 0 (`Vec Claim`) in lowered out/*.clj. NB: 41 = the (Vec Claim) GENERIC-site
;;     count specifically; the resolver's 116 = ALL type refs across all types. 41 ⊂ 116 — do not conflate.
;;   - lowered KEEPS 4 single-param ^Claim hints (kernel.clj:38,70,74,77) — so text-on-lowered is NOT
;;     "blind to Claim"; it is blind ONLY to the (Vec Claim) GENERIC case (which erases to 0). VERIFIED.
;;   - thread-ids-i (kernel.bclj:254): the suffix `-i` is DISTINCTIVE — a SINGLE `tsearch thread-ids-i`
;;     catches every reference incl the UNQUALIFIED intra-kernel caller work-thread-ids-i (kernel.bclj:267).
;;     The substring trap is ONE-DIRECTIONAL (VERIFIED): grepping the SHORTER `thread-ids` over-matches,
;;     but grepping the LONGER `thread-ids-i` is clean -> NO backtrack needed on the minimal path.
;;   - thread-ids-i callers (verified live :callers): {main x3 (81,98,100) via k/, tools x2 (232,239)
;;     via k/, kernel work-thread-ids-i (267) via UNQUALIFIED} -> module set {main,tools,kernel}.
;;   - (c) RE-TARGET: kernel#Claim is a defrecord, NOT a callgraph node — VERIFIED 0 of 145 blast keys
;;     contain Claim (the original (c) GT did not exist). (c) now targets kernel#thread-ids-i, whose
;;     :blast closure is EXACTLY 7 members (VERIFIED): {kernel/work-thread-ids-i, main/-main, main/cmd-call,
;;     main/cmd-export, main/cmd-validate, main/dispatch, tools/call}.
;;   - unmodified corpus compiles: 11 built, 0 error(s). rename Claim Datum -> CLAIMS EDITED: 1 (verified site).

