                   "  L0 introduces callers in 3 modules {kernel,main,tools}; 1 classify-read PER region to map call-site -> enclosing
                    defn (kernel 254:267, main 74:100, tools 214:239)   (3 reads) -> frontier1 {work-thread-ids-i, cmd-export, cmd-validate, call}"
                   "L1: tsearch '(cmd-export|cmd-validate|work-thread-ids-i|call)' src/fram   (1: the WHOLE frontier in ONE alternation pass —
                    METHODOLOGY guard 2 permits single-pass alternation) + 1 classify-read main 252:302 (confirm tl/call in cmd-call; dispatch edges) -> frontier2 {dispatch, cmd-call}"
                   "L2: tsearch '(dispatch|cmd-call)' src/fram   (1: one alternation pass) + 1 classify-read main 322:323 (confirm (dispatch ...) in -main) -> frontier3 {-main}"
                   "L3: tsearch '-main' src/fram   (1: no internal callers -> FIXPOINT, no new module, no read)"]
                  :justification
                  "Text holds NO transitive structure. A correct closure MUST be a hand-run BFS, but FRONTIER-BATCHED: ONE alternation
                   search per BFS LEVEL (not one per node — single-pass alternation is the methodology's own stated fair baseline) + ONE
                   classify-read per NEW caller-module-region per level. The closure spans 4 BFS levels -> 4 searches + 5 reads = 9 ops.
                   This is the call-graph fan-in the agent must rebuild — exactly the structure the graph pre-computed in one fixpoint."
                  :concrete-count "9 ops (4 searches + 5 reads), computed model-free from the callgraph level structure by text_bfs_cost.clj;
                                   the scripted hand-BFS in text_reconstruct.sh reproduces the SAME 9. A single falsifiable number, not '>=N'."
                  :anti-strawman "The BFS is the minimal correct algorithm, not a flail. We charge ONE search per frontier LEVEL (batched
                                  alternation), NOT one per node — charging a separate grep per node would inflate text and is rejected (must-fix #5)."}
   :verdict "GRAPH 1 (HYPOTHETICAL — :reaches unbuilt) vs TEXT 9 (frontier-batched: 4 searches + 5 reads), same 7-member closure. The gap is
             the call-graph fan-in size the graph pre-paid in one fixpoint. SEGREGATED from the live a/b rows: graph cost HYPOTHETICAL, text MEASURED."
   :measured-by "callgraph over emitted EDN: :blast[<kernel#thread-ids-i>] | length => 7; text_bfs_cost.clj => 9 (4 searches + 5 reads, frontier-batched)"}

