   :ground-truth-source {:via "resolved type refs: every :- (Vec Claim)/(Vec k/Claim) annotation whose inner type ultimate-resolves to kernel Claim"
                         :sites-measured 41
                         :sites-split "20 (Vec Claim) + 21 (Vec k/Claim) = 41  (VERIFIED). 41 = the (Vec Claim) GENERIC-site count
                                       specifically; the resolver's 116 = ALL type refs across ALL types. 41 ⊂ 116 — do not conflate."
                         :note "resolve.clj resolve-types-in-bracket! (205) + walk-type (191) carries each annotation's refers_to to the Claim node"}
   :graph {:ops 1
           :served :layer-a-hypothetical
           :served-note "GRAPH COST HYPOTHETICAL (the :type-refs op does NOT exist — VERIFIED {:error \"unknown op\"}).
                         1 is what the live :type-refs WOULD cost. VISUALLY SEGREGATED from a/b."
           :sequence ["gquery :type-refs {:inner <kernel#Claim> :ctor Vec}  (1: leaves with a (Vec ...) annotation whose inner type
                       refers_to kernel#Claim)  -- AVAILABLE ONLY ONCE the daemon adds :type-refs (see :live-cd-path)"]
           :note "the type reference is a first-class edge in the graph; it survives lowering BECAUSE the graph is over source identity."}
   :text-minimal {:headline "COST comparison on SOURCE (the substrate a competent engineer chooses when source is available)"
                  :source-subcase  {:ops 3
                                    :sequence
                                    ["tsearch '\\(Vec (k/)?Claim\\)' src/fram   (1: a SINGLE alternation regex catches BOTH spellings
                                      (Vec Claim) + (Vec k/Claim) in ONE pass — alias known, warm session)"
                                     "tread the hits to confirm each inner Claim is the KERNEL Claim, not a coincidental same-named type   (1)"
                                     "tread the few annotation sites whose form spans lines to confirm the parameter binding   (1)"]
                                    :justification "On SOURCE the annotations are visible tokens, so text CAN answer — one alternation
                                                    search + reads to confirm the inner type is kernel's Claim. 3 ops, correct.
                                                    Re-priced DOWN from 4 (alias amortized; both spellings in one pass)."
                                    :result "GRAPH 1 (hypothetical) vs TEXT-on-source 3, BOTH CORRECT — a COST win."}
                  :lowered-subcase {:precondition "ONLY applies when SOURCE IS UNAVAILABLE (the deployed-tooling-reads-lowered scenario,
                                                   matching tier-1's own concession). NOT the default — source-vs-source is the headline."
                                    :ops "1 retrieval -> WRONG for the GENERIC case"
                                    :sequence ["tsearch '\\(Vec Claim\\)' out/fram   (1: returns 0 — (Vec Claim) annotations ERASED at lowering)"]
                                    :scoped-claim "text-on-lowered CANNOT recover the (Vec Claim) GENERIC-parameter fns (these erase to 0 —
