                 the kernel caller), report the accuracy gap, not just op-count"
  :cheap-and-wrong "an arm that reaches the WRONG answer cheaply is scored a LOSS on that task, regardless of op-count"
  :hypothetical-segregation "c/d graph cost is a labeled HYPOTHETICAL (unbuilt op); NEVER blended into a like-for-like ladder with live a/b"}

 ;; ---- HONEST framing (no strawman in EITHER direction) ----
 :honest-framing
 {:layer-a-is-a-proof "Layer A removes the agent confound BY REMOVING THE AGENT -> it is a structural LOWER-BOUND PROOF about this corpus,
                       not a measurement. The headline EMPIRICAL claim is Layer B (real agents, N>=10). We do NOT pass authored A numbers as measured."
  :graph-pre-pays "the graph projects + resolves refers_to + maintains it incrementally (S1/S3) ONCE — paid VISIBLY here as the setup
                   projection (:graph-setup), MEASURED ~37s. The per-query advantage holds in a WARM session (the precondition); a COLD
                   single-question session LOSES. That cheap per-query cost IS what 'reasons faster in a context window' means."
  :amortization-symmetric "we amortize the graph's setup AND the text arm's alias-learning — same warm-session frame for both (NOT
                           asymmetric amortization favoring the graph). The :learned-alias map is given to both arms at setup."
  :alternation-allowed "a SINGLE alternation regex is ONE search pass = 1 op (a real engineer writes `rg '(k/)?Claim'`). Forbidding it
                        would inflate the text count; anti-gaming is about COMPOUND COMMANDS, not single-pass alternation. Text re-priced DOWN accordingly."
  :concede-trivial-local "task :cal is a TIE (grep is one op too); the graph's advantage is structural/cross-module/transitive ONLY"
  :concede-cd-hypothetical "tasks c/d are NOT live-served (:reaches/:type-refs are 'unknown op' — VERIFIED); their graph cost is a labeled
                            HYPOTHETICAL, VISUALLY SEGREGATED, NOT a measured op and NOT a text re-parse (which would invalidate the arm)"
  :concede-isolated-sed "task e: a perfect single sed over SOURCE catches all Claim tokens and recompiles clean (the file arm wins the
                         stand-alone rename in isolation). The graph win is identity O(1) + zero-miss-by-construction."
  :text-baseline-is-minimal-correct "re-derived DOWN to the ripgrep floor (a:4->2, b:5->2, d-source:4->3) with alternation + known alias.
                                     Each op tied to a MEASURED obstacle. A skeptic attacking it as inflated must lose."
  :graph-genuinely-queries "the LIVE graph arm calls the same daemon a deployed agent would, over the wire, off MATERIALIZED refers_to;
                            VERIFIED nonempty for a AND b; task b is KEYED ON THE REFERENCE, not the answer. NOT hand-fed, NOT re-parsing text."
  :not-wall-clock "wall-clock is recorded but NEVER headlined — confounded by model speed, JVM warmup, serialization latency"
  :lsp-concession "an LSP on the SOURCE language sees value-level callers fine; the categorical text loss is on the (Vec Claim) GENERIC
                   references ERASED at lowering (task d, source-UNAVAILABLE sub-case) + COST on cross-module/transitive"
  :c-ground-truth-fixed "(c) RE-TARGETED from kernel#Claim (a defrecord — NO blast key, GT did not exist) to kernel#thread-ids-i
                         (a real defn, :blast closure = 7, VERIFIED). The text BFS count is a CONCRETE number, not an unfalsifiable '>=N'."}

